&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Kasa&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kasa is the leading tech-enabled hotel and apartment hotel brand and manager. We partner with owners of multifamily and boutique hospitality properties to deliver stylish, professionally managed accommodations to business and leisure travelers alike. We took the best that hotels and short-term rentals had to offer and created a new class of hospitality that is well-priced, reliable, and offers a large selection of great locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike traditional hotel operators, we prioritize automation, AI-driven pricing, and data-driven decision-making to optimize revenue and improve guest experiences. Behind the scenes, we build technology that combines with our innovative operations to grow a globally scalable offering that delivers high-quality stays to guests. Our guests enjoy seamless check-ins, caring service, and attractive amenities — and if anything comes up, our on-site and remote guest experience team is available throughout their stay, ensuring our hospitality is rarely seen but always felt.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a critical leadership opportunity reporting to the Chief Investment and Development Officer, where you will take on a transformative role in driving Kasa’s portfolio expansion as a &lt;strong&gt;Real Estate Growth Executive&lt;/strong&gt;. In this role, you will be responsible for securing managed units through new unit launches, hotel conversions, hotel development, and acquisition while also participating in high-value, strategic growth initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You bring unmatched expertise in sourcing, negotiating, and closing complex transactions at scale. With an extensive network of property owners, lenders, and brokers, you will lead deal-making efforts for apartment, apartment-hotel and traditional hotel assets, leveraging innovative structures to minimize risk and maximize financial outcomes for both Kasa and our partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a forward-thinking, results-oriented professional who thrives in a dynamic, entrepreneurial environment and is passionate about shaping the future of real estate and hospitality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is in our Real Estate department. The mission of the department is to grow Kasa&#39;s national and global footprint by partnering with multifamily, hotel, and apart-hotel developers and owners. We achieve this mission by demonstrating the tremendous value we create for our partners through our high-margin and flexible operating model. Unlike traditional hospitality operators, we partner with property owners across a wide set of markets, property types, unit types, and deal structures, including, traditional management agreements, revenue share leases, centralized services agreements, and property acquisitions. As a result, our dynamic operations, proprietary tech, and cost structure make Kasa the one-stop partner for property owners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Members of the team have diverse backgrounds in real estate private equity, finance, investment sales, construction, and hotel business development. Kasa team members are passionate about building a platform that delivers value to property owners and serves guests seeking trustworthy, well-priced accommodations in great locations.&lt;/p&gt;
